{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3354197,"name":"Josh P","username":"BigJ","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bigj/{size}/93596_2.png","created_at":"2024-04-07T19:41:25.352Z","cooked":"<p>Anyone out there have a solution they use for rapid remapping of controls or saving layouts besides hard-editing the current controller mappings? We have a desire to do this to let prospective drivers remap their controls while practicing. Things like swapping buttons and inverting axes. A cursory search of <span class="abbreviation">CD<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Chief Delphi"></template></span> didn’t find anything for me.</p>
<p>Ideas I have come up with so far are separate classes that just contain the mapping and keeping mappings in json files or similar.</p>
<p>Once drivers are picked we would go back to one solid mapped control layout.</p>
<p>Programming team support is OK/expected for this solution, just wondering if anyone out there has already tackled this problem before I think about it harder.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":3,"updated_at":"2024-04-07T19:41:25.352Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":81,"readers_count":80,"score":36.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":461590,"topic_slug":"controller-loadouts-remapping","display_username":"Josh P","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":7632,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/controller-loadouts-remapping/461590/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3354423,"name":"Tim Winters","username":"ArchdukeTim","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/archduketim/{size}/256125_2.png","created_at":"2024-04-07T23:59:24.185Z","cooked":"<p>I would so something like</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">interface DriverControls {
  public Trigger getAction1ButtonPressed();
  public Trigger getAction2ButtonPressed();
}

public class Driver1Controls implements DriverControls {
  public Trigger getAction1ButtonPressed() {
    return commandXboxController.x();
  }

  public Trigger getAction2ButtonPressed() {
    return commandXboxController.y();
  }
}

public class Driver2Controls implements DriverControls {
  public Trigger getAction1ButtonPressed() {
    return commandXboxController.a();
  }

  public Trigger getAction2ButtonPressed() {
    return commandXboxController.b();
  }
}
</code></pre>
